 locked domain profile
+
+This is an isolated SignalCore domain profile. It is not a Roblox plugin, MCP server,
+Luau compiler, content generator, animation engine, Blender implementation, playtest
+environment or DataStore emulator.
+
+It compiles authorized Roblox Studio requests into minimal, budgeted, validated
+orchestration contracts for external engines.
+
+## Activation boundary
+
+The existing short-lived HMAC-SHA256 Studio activation envelope remains mandatory.
+The profile is hidden from normal skill discovery and cannot be activated through a
+CLI flag, IDE prompt, Codex, Claude Code, Cursor, VS Code, Gemini CLI or raw JSON.
+
+The external Studio bridge must provide process attestation, Place/project identity,
+an allowed capability subset, TTL, signature and a single-use nonce.
+
+## Implemented profile systems
+
+- typed compound `RobloxTaskState` V2
+- 33-capability versioned graph
+- pinned engine registry and provider-independent model registry
+- role/capability certification matrix and model certification harness
+- deterministic zero-model skip path
+- ambiguity, risk, sandbox, privacy and budget gates
+- dynamic tool loading and one-round-trip compiler policy
+- Evidence Ledger V3, delta cache and typed artifact caches
+- multimodal representative-frame selection
+- Context Knapsack V2
+- workflow DAGs, checkpoints, repair capsules and rollback policy
+- cross-engine response and validator contracts
+- Telemetry V2 and trace/replay
+- controlled A/B/C/D benchmark
+
+## Quick local checks
+
+```bash
+python -m unittest discover -s tests -q
+python benchmarks/roblox_profile_benchmark.py --cases 500 --output roblox-profile-500.json
+```
+
+Current profile-specific suite: **149/149 PASS**. See
+[`BENCHMARK_RESULTS.md`](BENCHMARK_RESULTS.md) and
+[`COMPLETION_REPORT.md`](COMPLETION_REPORT.md).
+
+## Security boundary
+
+This gate prevents accidental activation. It is not DRM and cannot protect against a
+local operating-system user who can modify SignalCore or read the pairing secret.
+Production bridge implementations should use the OS credential store and native
+process attestation.
+
+External asset metadata, tool output, model output and generated artifacts are data,
+not trusted instructions. Critical workflows remain fail-closed without measured
+certification, required evidence, sandbox availability and independent validation.
